 enormous public controversy that resulted, and he demonstrates that the Gassner episode yields important insights into the German Enlightenment and Counter-Enlightenment, the limitations of eighteenth-century debate, and the ongoing role of magic and belief in an age of scientific enlightenment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aEnlightenmentxGermany. 0aEnlightenmentzGermany. 0aExorcismxHistoryx18th centuryxGermany. 0aExorcismzGermanyxHistoryy18th century. 0aExorcismexHistoirex18e sièclexAllemagne. 0aFaith and reasonxChristianityxHistory of doctrinesx18th century. 0aFaith and reasonxChristianityxHistory of doctrinesy18th century. 0aFoi et raisonxChristianismexHistoire des doctrinesx18e siècle. 0aSiècle des lumièresxAllemagne. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300130133423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300130133.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles